        <div class="modal-body">
            <span class="modal-tag">Semester Project — IoT & Accessibility</span>
            <h2>Assistive Device for the Visually Impaired</h2>
            <div class="modal-meta">
                <span><i class="far fa-calendar"></i> Sep 2024 — Jan 2025</span>
                <span><i class="fas fa-school"></i> EURECOM</span>
            </div>

            <div class="modal-section">
                <h3>Context & Challenge</h3>
                <p>Visually impaired people face major navigation challenges daily. This project aimed to design a <strong>low-cost, portable assistive device</strong>. It provides real-time spatial feedback using haptic and audio indicators.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="modal-section">
                <h3>How It Works</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li><strong>Video acquisition:</strong> A camera module on a Raspberry Pi 4 captures the environment in real time.</li>
                    <li><strong>Image processing:</strong> Python scripts analyze the video to detect obstacles and estimate distances.</li>
                    <li><strong>Haptic feedback:</strong> Vibration motors give directional cues. The vibration intensity increases as obstacles get closer.</li>
                    <li><strong>Audio signals:</strong> Sound alerts warn the user about critical obstacles or provide navigation instructions.</li>
                </ol>
            </div>

            <div class="modal-section">
                <h3>Hardware Used</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Raspberry Pi 4 (Main processing unit)</li>
                    <li>Pi Camera Module (Environment capture)</li>
                    <li>Vibration motors (Haptic feedback)</li>
                    <li>GPIO wiring</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-section">
                <h3>Technologies</h3>
                <div class="modal-tech">
                    <span>Python</span><span>Raspberry Pi 4</span><span>Camera Module</span><span>GPIO</span><span>Haptic Sensors</span><span>Embedded Systems</span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Modal: EGM -->
    <div class="project-modal" id="modal-egm">
        <button class="modal-close" aria-label="Close"><i class="fas fa-xmark"></i></button>
        <div class="modal-banner">
            <img src="./img-egm.png" alt="EGM Internship Visuals">
        </div>
        <div class="modal-body">
            <span class="modal-tag">Data Science Internship</span>
            <h2>Data Processing & Automation — EGM</h2>
            <div class="modal-meta">
                <span><i class="far fa-calendar"></i> Jun 2025 — Jul 2025</span>
                <span><i class="fas fa-building"></i> EGM, Sophia Antipolis</span>
                <a href="https://github.com/charlysejobe/egm_internship" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="project-link"><i class="fab fa-github"></i> View on GitHub</a>
            </div>

            <div class="modal-section">
                <h3>Context & Challenge</h3>
                <p>EGM is a sustainable tech company. I worked with data from environmental sensors like the <em>eNose</em> gas detector and the <em>Pixelo</em>. The existing evaluation process was manual and slow. Engineers had to extract data, calculate metrics, and format reports by hand.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="modal-section">
                <h3>What I Built</h3>
                <p>To solve this bottleneck, I designed and deployed an automated Python data pipeline:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Modular data pipeline:</strong> Created a scalable Python architecture to ingest and analyze raw CSV sensor data automatically.</li>
                    <li><strong>Data processing:</strong> Used the <em>Pandas</em> library to clean, structure, and manipulate datasets efficiently.</li>
                    <li><strong>Automated visualizations:</strong> Integrated <em>Matplotlib</em> to calculate key metrics (baselines, normalizations, average curves) and generate formatted graphs.</li>
                    <li><strong>Report generation:</strong> The script automatically compiles and exports visual reports into specific folders. They are instantly ready for the management team.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="modal-section">
                <h3>Lab Work & Hardware Testing</h3>
                <p>I handled physical sensors (eNose, Pixelo) and managed the full data chain, from physical measurement to automated analysis.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="modal-section">
                <h3>Impact</h3>
                <p>The automation tool reduced manual tasks and improved data quality. It allowed the engineering team to focus on analysis rather than data preparation.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="modal-section">
                <h3>Technologies</h3>
                <div class="modal-tech">
                    <span>Python</span><span>Pandas</span><span>Matplotlib</span><span>Data Automation</span><span>IoT Sensor Data</span><span>Lab Testing</span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

